laboratory_examinations.findings: PT (prothrombin time) is 26.1 sec (reference range: 22.0 - 35.0 sec)

Small amount of fluid around the pancreatic body and tail, smooth pancreatic duct with normal caliber, 7 mm cystic lesion adjacent to main duct, numerous gallstones, normal intra- and extra-hepatic bile ducts, 12-mm lesion of hepatic segment IV consistent with hemangioma, tiny simple cyst of the right kidney, no concerning hepatic lesions.
